import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['cx'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of cx?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cy', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['cy'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['cy'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of cy?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("cy")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='cx', y='cy', hue='name', palette='tab20')

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='cx', ascending=False).head(5)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='name', y='cx', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What are the top 5 locations with the highest cx values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('CX Value')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
